# YouTube Video Transcriber and Q&A

This project provides a tool to fetch YouTube video transcripts, build a retriever for Q&A, and interact with the transcript via a Streamlit app, FastAPI backend, and a Chrome extension.

---

## Directory Structure

```bash
.
├── api
│   └── app.py
├── app
│   └── app.py
├── extension
│   ├── icon.png
│   ├── manifest.json
│   ├── popup.js
│   ├── styles.css
│   └── tell_me.html
├── .env
├── makefile
├── README
└── requirements.txt
```

---

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/accelbia/transcription-rag-demo
cd transcription-rag-demo
```
### 2. Install Dependencies
Create a virtual environment and install the required Python packages:

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt)
```

### 3. Set Up Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the root directory and add the following:
```bash
OPENAI_API_KEY=<your_openai_api_key>
```

## Running the Project
### Using Makefile Commands
The project includes a makefile for easy execution of different components:

#### 1. Run the FastAPI Backend:
```bash
make run-api
```
This starts the API server on http://localhost:8000. Access the documentation at http://localhost:8000/docs.

#### 2. Run the Streamlit App:
```bash
make run-streamlit
```
This starts the Streamlit app on http://localhost:8501.

## Features
- Streamlit App: Enter a YouTube video ID, view the transcript, and ask questions about the video.
FastAPI Backend: Provides endpoints for fetching transcripts and answering questions.
Chrome Extension: Extracts YouTube video IDs from active tabs and allows Q&A directly from the browser.

- FastAPI Backend: Provides endpoints for fetching transcripts and answering questions.

- Chrome Extension: Extracts YouTube video IDs from active tabs and allows Q&A directly from the browser.

## Notes
Ensure the .env file is not committed to version control (already included in .gitignore).
The Chrome extension requires enabling developer mode in Chrome to load it.